aa(lp383
VPersonally, I feel enormously grateful
p384
aVto have lived through the age of cheap oil.
p385
aVI've been astonishingly lucky, we've been astonishingly lucky.
p386
aVBut let us honor what it has bought us,
p387
aVand move forward from this point.
p388
aVBecause if we cling to it, and continue to assume
p389
aVthat it can underpin our choices,
p390
aVthe future that it presents to us is one which is really unmanageable.
p391
aVAnd by loving and leaving all that oil has done for us,
p392
aVand that the Oil Age has done for us,
p393
aVwe are able to then begin the creation
p394
aVof a world which is more resilient,
p395
aVmore nourishing,
p396
